To extract a three character code like "1Jn" from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm", you can use the following regular expression:

```
^(\d+)-([a-zA-Z0-9]{3})\.usfm$
```

This regex will match filenames that start with a number, followed by a dash, then three characters (upper or lower case letters or digits), and finally the ".usfm" extension. The parentheses around the second group capture the three character code into Group 2 for later use if needed.
